President Obama recently met with DHS Secretary Janet Napolitano and TSA Administrator John S. Pistole to discuss the enhancements made to aviation and surface transportation security. The briefing, which was part of the President's regular counterterrorism and homeland security briefing, was not prompted by any specific threat. The President was updated on the strategic plans of the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), particularly efforts to improve security in mass transit and passenger rail. The TSA has made progress in enhancing security through improved technology and procedures, stronger partnerships with transportation stakeholders, and increased engagement with the international community. The President reiterated the importance of prioritizing mass transit and passenger rail security and offered support to Secretary Napolitano and Administrator Pistole.